This paper discusses the interplay between machine learning and optimization, specifically focusing on supervised learning and convex optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses boosting, which is a popular machine learning algorithm, and its relation to optimization techniques. This could potentially fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of dual-averaging scheme, which is a technique used in optimization, suggesting a possible fit for cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper evaluates the generalization performance of the proposed algorithm, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
